  	<p style="text-align:left; font-size: 18px;"> Below are different codes you might need for this task. </p>
    <ul>
    <li>To change the <b>color</b> of the text, use  <img src="color.png" alt="color" height="18">.  The "#5F1BDA" is the HEX color code and can be any color code. To define the <b>background color of the text</b>, change <b>color to background-color</b>.</li>
    <li>To change the <b>alignment</b> of the text use <img src="align.png" alt="align" height="18">.  The alignment can be either <i>left, center, or right.</i></li>
    <li>To <b>decorate</b> your text, use <img src="decorate.png" alt="decorate" height="18">. The three options are <i>overline, line-through, and underline.</i></li>
    <li>To <b>transform</b> your text, use <img src="transform.png" alt="transform" height="18">. The three options are <i>uppercase, lowercase, and capitalize.</i> </li>
    <li>To add a <b>shadow</b> to your text, use <img src="shadow.png" alt="shadow" height="18">.  The numbers define how <i>big</i> your shadow is. </li>
     </ul>   
     
     <p>Using your notes and the information above, change each paragraph to the <b>designated style</b>, using the designated <b>selector type</b>. When you are finished, take a screenshot that includes your code and the output and put it in your notes.</p>
